WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:51.849 --> 01:54.432
Yeah, I worked
in a barber shop,

01:54.557 --> 01:57.557
But I never considered
myself a barber.

01:57.682 --> 02:02.099
I stumbled into it well,
married into it, more precisely.

02:02.224 --> 02:06.182
It wasn't my establishment.
Like the fella says, I only work here.

02:09.514 --> 02:11.181
The dump was 200 feet square...

02:11.473 --> 02:14.181
With three chairs,
or stations, as we call 'em,

02:14.473 --> 02:16.598
Even though there are only
two of us working.

02:16.723 --> 02:19.515
But this is my point.

02:19.598 --> 02:22.931
My point is that these traders and trappers
would come to this country,

02:23.056 --> 02:25.223
Get their pelts
and their gold "ignots"

02:25.515 --> 02:28.431
Frank Raffo, my brother-in-law,
was the principal barber.

02:28.515 --> 02:29.931
Man, could he talk.

02:31.848 --> 02:35.598
Maybe if you're 11 or 12 years old,
Frank's got an interesting point of view,

02:35.681 --> 02:38.140
But sometimes
it got on my nerves.

02:38.348 --> 02:40.140
Not that I complained,
mind you.

02:40.223 --> 02:42.680
Like I said, he was
the principal Barber.

02:43.680 --> 02:46.222
Frank's father August
they called him Guzzi

02:46.347 --> 02:48.972
Had worked the heads up
in Santa Rosa for 35 years...

02:49.097 --> 02:51.889
Until his ticker stopped
in the middle of a junior flattop.

02:51.972 --> 02:55.264
He left the shop to Frankie free and clear,

02:55.347 --> 02:57.972
And that seemed to satisfy
all of Frank's ambitions

02:58.055 --> 03:00.847
Cutting the hair
and chewing the fat.

03:00.972 --> 03:03.722
Me, I don't talk much.

03:08.680 --> 03:10.554
I just cut the hair.

03:18.845 --> 03:21.803
It says here that the russians
exploded an a-bomb...

03:21.887 --> 03:24.803
And there's not a damn thing
we can do about it.

03:27.345 --> 03:29.345
How do you like them apples?

03:35.178 --> 03:38.345
Being a barber is a lot like
being a bar man or a soda jerk.

03:38.637 --> 03:42.803
There's not much to it once
you've learned the basic moves.

03:42.928 --> 03:44.887
For the kids, there's the butch,
or the heinie,

03:44.970 --> 03:46.927
The flattop, the ivy,

03:47.011 --> 03:48.802
The crew, the vanguard,

03:48.886 --> 03:50.302
The junior contour...

03:50.386 --> 03:53.844
And occasionally
the executive contour.

03:55.302 --> 03:59.052
Lived in a little bungalow
on napa street.

03:59.136 --> 04:00.927
The place was okay, I guess.

04:01.011 --> 04:04.135
Had an electric icebox,
a gas hearth...

04:04.260 --> 04:07.218
And a garbage grinde
built into the sink.

04:07.343 --> 04:09.676
You might say I had it made.

04:09.801 --> 04:12.343
Oh, year,
there was one other thing.

04:14.176 --> 04:16.593
Doris kept the books
at Nirdlingers,

04:16.676 --> 04:19.050
A small department store
on main street.

04:19.134 --> 04:21.591
Doris liked the work,
accounting.

04:21.675 --> 04:24.259
She liked knowing
where everything stood

04:24.342 --> 04:28.175
And she got a ten percent employee
discount on whatever she wanted

04:28.300 --> 04:29.800
Nylon stockings,

04:29.925 --> 04:32.717
Makeup and perfume.

04:34.634 --> 04:37.300
Doris and I went to church
once a week.

04:38.300 --> 04:40.759
Usually Tuesday night.

04:47.884 --> 04:50.759
Doris wasn't big
on divine worship,

04:50.842 --> 04:54.090
And I doubt if she believed
in life everlasting.

04:54.173 --> 04:57.132
She'd most likely tell you
that our reward is on this earth,

04:57.215 --> 04:59.923
And bingo is probably
the extent of it.

05:00.007 --> 05:01.632
B-7

05:01.715 --> 05:02.923
Watch you card,
honey.

05:03.007 --> 05:05.923
I wasn't crazy
about the game,

05:06.007 --> 05:08.090
But, I don't know,
it made her happy,

05:08.173 --> 05:11.298
And I found the setting
peaceful.

05:11.382 --> 05:12.798
Jesus. Bingo.

05:12.882 --> 05:14.090
Bingo!

05:15.257 --> 05:17.882
Doris's boss,
Big Dave Brewster,

05:18.007 --> 05:21.923
Was married to Ann Nirdlinger,
the department store heiress.

05:22.007 --> 05:24.214
Tonight they were coming over for dinner.

05:24.297 --> 05:26.047
As Doris said,

05:26.172 --> 05:28.589
We were entertaining.

05:31.631 --> 05:33.797
Me, I don't like
entertaining.

05:36.922 --> 05:38.881
- How you doin', Ed?
- Okay.

05:39.006 --> 05:40.797
Take your coat, Ann?

05:40.881 --> 05:44.339
The japs had us pinned down
on Buna for somethin' like six weeks.

05:44.588 --> 05:47.713
I gotta tell ya,
I thought we had it tough,
but we had supply.

05:47.838 --> 05:52.171
The japs were eatin' bugs
and grubs and thistles.

05:52.296 --> 05:55.130
Anyway, one day
we bust off the beach...

05:55.213 --> 05:59.254
And we find Arney Bragg,
this kid missin' on recon.

05:59.337 --> 06:02.087
The japs had eaten the son of a bitch.

06:02.170 --> 06:04.212
If you'll pardon the, uh...

06:04.337 --> 06:08.087
Anyway, he was a scrawny, pimply kid,
nothin' to write home about.

06:08.170 --> 06:10.170
I mean, I never woulda,
you know.

06:12.712 --> 06:15.087
So, what do I say, honey?

06:15.170 --> 06:18.004
What do I say
when I don't like dinner?

06:18.087 --> 06:19.587
Come on.
What do I say?

06:19.670 --> 06:22.170
I say,
"Arney Bragg, again?"

06:27.129 --> 06:29.044
Arney Bragg, again?

06:35.378 --> 06:38.210
- Were you in the service, Ed?
- No, Dave, I wasn't.

06:38.335 --> 06:41.752
Ed was 4-f on account
of his fallen arches.

06:46.668 --> 06:47.918
That's tough.

06:48.002 --> 06:49.918
That's... That's tough.

06:55.127 --> 06:59.710
Yeah, I guess Doris liked
all that he-man stuff.

06:59.835 --> 07:02.084
Sometimes I had the feeling that

07:02.167 --> 07:05.084
She and Big Dave were a lot closer
than they let on.

07:05.167 --> 07:07.792
The signs were all there,
plain enough.

07:17.876 --> 07:20.876
Not that I was gonna
prance about it, mind you.

07:21.001 --> 07:22.834
It's a free country.

07:24.584 --> 07:26.001
Holdin' down the porch area, Ed?

07:27.376 --> 07:30.166
- That's some wife you got there.
- Yeah.

07:31.166 --> 07:33.083
She's a rare one.

07:35.332 --> 07:36.957
So, how's business,
Dave?

07:37.290 --> 07:40.082
Oh, uh, couldn't be better.

07:40.165 --> 07:43.124
These are boom times
in retailin', Ed.

07:43.165 --> 07:45.624
We're openin' another store
over there on carson,

07:45.707 --> 07:48.915
Big Dave's annex.
Now, this is strictly haberdashery.

07:48.999 --> 07:52.124
It's casual wear, pajamas,
ladies' undergarments and foundations,

07:52.249 --> 07:53.999
That type of thing.

07:55.999 --> 08:00.040
As a matter of fact,
I'm thinkin' of makin' Doris the comptroller.

08:04.165 --> 08:06.581
Listen, when the annex opens up,
you gotta stop by.

08:06.664 --> 08:08.706
Maybe we can update your suit
a little bit, huh?

08:13.331 --> 08:15.789
Course, you're in
the smock all day.

08:17.914 --> 08:20.080
Where do you get those things,
anyway?

08:20.163 --> 08:23.622
Specialty store
down in Sacramento.

08:34.871 --> 08:36.330
You tie your own flies.

08:36.621 --> 08:40.078
I mean, if you're really serious,
you tie your own flies.

08:40.162 --> 08:41.621
You do, uh...

08:41.703 --> 08:43.996
I know. It's meticulous.
I know.

08:44.121 --> 08:46.746
People say, hey, you can
buy flies at the store.

08:46.829 --> 08:49.954
The point is, there's a certain art
to the process.

08:50.079 --> 08:52.537
The point is not merely to provide.

08:52.662 --> 08:57.037
Let me point out, these fish are not
as dumb as you might think.

08:57.162 --> 08:59.162
Sure.
Go to the store.

08:59.287 --> 09:02.662
Describe to the man
where you will be fishing and for what,

09:02.787 --> 09:07.704
And then you might as well have the man
sell you the goddamned fish, Ed.

09:07.829 --> 09:08.954
My point is,

09:09.079 --> 09:12.119
This is a man who knows nothing,
no matter how much you tell him.

09:12.202 --> 09:14.994
- So sell him the goddamned fish, Ed.
- Yeah.

09:16.577 --> 09:17.619
Okay.

09:18.660 --> 09:20.619
Who gets the privilege?

09:20.702 --> 09:22.535
We're just closing, friend.

09:22.785 --> 09:24.535
Oh, happy days.

09:25.160 --> 09:28.535
I wish I was doing well enough
to turn away business.

09:28.660 --> 09:32.660
What's the problem, friend?
This is a business establishment with posted hours.

09:32.827 --> 09:34.452
More power to ya, brother.

09:34.577 --> 09:35.619
The public be damned.

09:35.785 --> 09:36.619
Hey...

09:36.702 --> 09:38.577
I'll take care of him.
You go ahead, Frank.

09:38.660 --> 09:40.660
Have a seat, mister.

09:40.785 --> 09:43.660
- You sure, Eddie?
- Yeah, yeah, go ahead.

09:46.784 --> 09:48.909
In your ear, mister.

09:51.034 --> 09:54.034
Oh, those fiery
Mediterraneans.

09:54.993 --> 09:58.243
Uh, say, uh,
not so fast there, brother.

10:00.826 --> 10:01.951
Pretty good, eh?

10:02.034 --> 10:03.950
Fools even the experts.

10:04.033 --> 10:07.533
One hundred percent human hair.
Handcrafted by Jacques

10:07.658 --> 10:09.242
Of San Francisco.

10:09.325 --> 10:12.533
I'd hate to have to tell you
what I paid for it.

10:12.658 --> 10:15.075
Yeah, it's a nice rug.

10:15.158 --> 10:17.074
I'm payin' it down
on the installment plan.

10:17.157 --> 10:21.116
A lot of folks live
with the pate exposed.

10:21.241 --> 10:23.657
They say the dames
think it's sexy,

10:23.782 --> 10:26.907
But for my money
it's just not good groomin'.

10:26.991 --> 10:30.782
And groomin' my friend,
is probably the most important thing in business.

10:30.866 --> 10:33.324
After personality, of course.

10:34.324 --> 10:36.782
Creighton Tolliver.
Pleased to know ya.

10:37.866 --> 10:39.282
Ed Crane.

10:40.282 --> 10:42.657
So, what brings you
to Santa Rosa?

10:42.782 --> 10:45.949
A goose, my friend.
I was chasin' a wild goose.

10:47.699 --> 10:49.656
Ed, have you ever heard
of venture capital?

10:49.781 --> 10:52.240
Risk money.
Very speculative.

10:52.323 --> 10:56.739
Except that in certain situations
it's not, see.

10:56.822 --> 10:58.947
I thought I had
a prospect here

10:59.030 --> 11:03.655
Well, I make the haul up...
And this lousy so-and-so tells me...

11:03.780 --> 11:05.614
That the situation has changed.

11:05.739 --> 11:09.239
All of his capital's tied up
in expansion plans of his own.

11:09.322 --> 11:12.072
Thank you mother.
Pop goes another bubble.

11:12.155 --> 11:15.030
It's only the biggest business opportunity
since Henry Ford,

11:15.155 --> 11:17.905
And I can't seem
to interest a soul.

11:17.989 --> 11:19.030
Is that right?

11:19.155 --> 11:21.114
It's called dry cleaning.

11:22.654 --> 11:25.279
You heard me right, brother.
Dry cleaning.

11:25.363 --> 11:28.154
Wash without water.

11:28.279 --> 11:31.904
No suds. No tumple.
No stress on the clothes.

11:31.988 --> 11:34.779
It's all done
with chemicals, friend.

11:34.821 --> 11:36.613
And here's the capper...

11:36.696 --> 11:38.029
No shrinkage.

11:38.988 --> 11:40.779
That's right.

11:40.821 --> 11:42.113
Dry cleaning.

11:42.154 --> 11:45.321
All I need is $10,000
to open up the first store.

11:45.613 --> 11:50.195
Then I use its cash flow
to finance another, and so on,

11:50.320 --> 11:53.612
Leapfrog, bootstrap myself
to a whole chain.

11:54.652 --> 11:56.152
Well, me and a partner.

11:57.819 --> 12:00.111
Cleanliness, friend.

12:00.236 --> 12:02.277
There's money in it.
There's a future.

12:02.361 --> 12:04.069
There's room to grow.

12:04.152 --> 12:07.319
Say, that looks pretty good.

12:07.611 --> 12:09.777
Let's see it
with the hairpiece on.

12:21.986 --> 12:23.777
Dry cleaning.

12:25.319 --> 12:28.735
Was I crazy
to be thinking about it?

12:28.818 --> 12:33.276
Was he a huckster or an opportunity,
the real Mccoy?

12:36.693 --> 12:40.984
My first instinct was
no, no, the whole idea was nuts.

12:41.109 --> 12:44.859
But maybe that was the instinct
that kept me locked in the barber shop,

12:44.984 --> 12:48.775
Nose against the exit
afraid to try turning the knob.

12:49.734 --> 12:51.067
- Honey?
- Hmm?

12:52.567 --> 12:54.650
Shave my legs, will ya?

12:59.983 --> 13:02.149
What if I could
get the money?

13:33.897 --> 13:36.106
It was clean.

13:36.772 --> 13:38.606
No water.

13:39.814 --> 13:41.606
Chemicals.

13:45.772 --> 13:47.606
Gimme a drag.

14:00.106 --> 14:01.772
Love ya, honey.

14:05.980 --> 14:07.605
What you...
uh, come in.

14:08.813 --> 14:11.896
Okay, yeah.
I'll see you tomorrow.

14:13.980 --> 14:15.771
Oh. I thought
you were the porter.

14:15.855 --> 14:17.855
Can I help ya?

14:17.980 --> 14:19.730
I'm Ed.

14:19.813 --> 14:21.812
Ed Crane.

14:24.104 --> 14:26.187
Um, I cut your hair today.

14:27.812 --> 14:29.062
I'm the barber.

14:29.145 --> 14:31.770
Jesus, yeah.
The barber.

14:31.854 --> 14:34.604
I didn't recognize you
without the smock.

14:34.729 --> 14:36.770
Did I leave somethin'
at the shop?

14:36.854 --> 14:39.269
No. No,
it's nothing like that.

14:39.353 --> 14:42.728
Um, I-I might be interested
in that business proposition.

14:45.894 --> 14:47.103
You got the dough?

14:47.144 --> 14:49.686
Well, I can get it.

14:49.811 --> 14:52.186
Come in. Come in!

14:52.311 --> 14:53.728
Sit down over there.

14:53.811 --> 14:56.186
- Coffee?
- No.

14:56.311 --> 14:59.561
Well, sit down,
make yourself comfortable.

15:01.311 --> 15:03.519
So tell me...

15:03.769 --> 15:08.311
Other than putting up the money, uh,
exactly what would you want the partner to, uh...

15:08.603 --> 15:10.060
Do?

15:10.143 --> 15:11.768
Hell, nothin'.

15:11.852 --> 15:16.101
You're gonna want to keep
tabs on your investment,
The running of the business,

15:16.184 --> 15:18.851
but I'm looking for a silent partner.

15:18.976 --> 15:22.017
I've done the research,
I've contacted the vendors.

15:22.142 --> 15:23.726
The deal is set.

15:23.809 --> 15:28.059
Disappear, if you'd like.
Check in whenever you want.

15:28.142 --> 15:31.642
I want the dough.
I don't take attendance.

15:31.767 --> 15:33.226
And how do we share the...

15:33.351 --> 15:35.601
Fifty-fifty,
straight down the line.

15:35.726 --> 15:37.934
You and me.
Finance and expertise.

15:38.976 --> 15:40.934
So you got the dough then,
do ya?

15:41.017 --> 15:43.100
I can have it in a week.

15:43.225 --> 15:45.308
The barber...

15:46.808 --> 15:50.266
Well, I thought this trip
was gonna be a bust.

15:50.558 --> 15:53.600
Just shows to go ya,
when one door slams shut,

15:53.641 --> 15:55.600
Another one opens.

15:55.641 --> 15:57.975
Here's to you, uh...

16:27.681 --> 16:29.264
Was that a pass?

16:30.598 --> 16:32.014
Maybe.

16:33.014 --> 16:34.764
Well, you're out of line, mister

16:36.681 --> 16:38.223
Not a problem.

16:38.306 --> 16:40.056
Way out of line.

16:40.139 --> 16:42.139
Right.

16:42.264 --> 16:44.056
Strictly business.

16:46.723 --> 16:48.097
Okay.

16:59.012 --> 17:01.762
I sent it to Dave
the next morning.

17:01.887 --> 17:03.596
Then I waited.

17:24.136 --> 17:26.511
- Frank?
- Huh?

17:29.345 --> 17:31.220
This hair.

17:32.220 --> 17:34.053
Yeah?

17:34.136 --> 17:35.928
You ever wonder about it?

17:37.303 --> 17:38.803
What do you mean?

17:39.970 --> 17:42.095
I don't know.

17:42.178 --> 17:44.636
How it keeps on coming.

17:46.053 --> 17:49.094
It just keeps growing.

17:49.177 --> 17:51.552
Yeah.
Lucky for us, huh, pal?

17:51.635 --> 17:52.759
No, I mean,

17:54.176 --> 17:56.259
It keeps growing,

17:57.134 --> 17:59.051
And it's part of us.

18:00.801 --> 18:03.593
And then we cut it off
and throw it away.

18:04.718 --> 18:07.634
Come on, Eddie.
You're gonna scare the kid.

18:15.843 --> 18:17.843
Okay, bud, you're through.

18:32.217 --> 18:35.133
I'm gonna take this hair
and throw it out in the dirt.

18:35.258 --> 18:37.133
What?

18:39.050 --> 18:42.007
I'm gonna mingle it
with common house dirt.

18:44.757 --> 18:47.507
What the hell
are you talking about?

18:50.757 --> 18:52.549
I don't know.
Skip it.

19:02.298 --> 19:04.256
Ed, gimme a zip.

19:04.340 --> 19:06.840
Where you going?

19:06.965 --> 19:11.090
Us. The party at Nirdlingers.
I told you last week.

19:11.215 --> 19:14.756
The Christmas push.

19:15.798 --> 19:17.590
Come on, get ready.

19:17.673 --> 19:18.965
It's important.

19:19.090 --> 19:22.215
Nah, you go ahead.
I'm not big on parties.

19:22.298 --> 19:25.590
Oh, don't be a grump.
Gimme a zip.

19:55.004 --> 19:57.088
Hey, uh, ain't you
in ladies' wear?

19:58.879 --> 20:01.629
Huh? Haven't I seen you
up in ladies' wear?

20:01.754 --> 20:03.920
I don't work here.
My wife does

20:05.337 --> 20:07.087
Uh-huh. Whew.
That's some beat, huh?

20:07.212 --> 20:08.753
Yeah.
Lucky for us, huh, pal?

20:08.837 --> 20:11.795
Check out the rack
on that broad in the angora.

20:12.795 --> 20:14.920
Ed, can I talk to you?

20:15.003 --> 20:16.087
Sure.

20:18.837 --> 20:19.920
Come in.

20:23.669 --> 20:25.836
Oh, sit down.

20:28.627 --> 20:30.961
Souvenired it off a jap
in New Guinea.

20:34.336 --> 20:38.293
Guess you're, uh, wonderin'
what Doris was so hot about.

20:43.835 --> 20:45.085
Havanas.

20:45.960 --> 20:47.918
My private stock.

20:49.335 --> 20:51.210
Romeo and Juliet.

21:10.042 --> 21:11.709
Ed, I...

21:16.333 --> 21:18.791
What is it, Dave?

21:23.124 --> 21:24.583
Ed, I've been weak.

21:24.666 --> 21:27.249
I've been weak.
The, uh...

21:29.333 --> 21:31.583
You're gonna burn yourself.

21:34.666 --> 21:35.916
Thanks.

21:35.999 --> 21:37.249
I, uh...

21:40.290 --> 21:41.832
Oh, Jesus.

21:45.582 --> 21:47.582
I've been carryin' on
with a married woman.

21:49.790 --> 21:51.915
No one you know.

21:52.040 --> 21:54.540
And now the, uh,

21:54.665 --> 21:56.998
The chickens are
comin' home to roost.

21:57.790 --> 21:59.707
I got a note.

21:59.790 --> 22:01.790
A blackmail note, you know.

22:01.873 --> 22:04.040
Come across,
or everybody knows.

22:06.331 --> 22:09.081
I guess you know
what that would do to me.

22:12.955 --> 22:14.621
I guess that would be
pretty awkward.

22:14.746 --> 22:16.288
Awkward?

22:16.580 --> 22:19.205
Yeah. Yeah.

22:19.288 --> 22:22.621
Ann would throw me
right out on my keister.

22:22.746 --> 22:25.913
I mean, it's her st...
It's her family's store, Ed.
It's her store.

22:25.996 --> 22:29.580
I serve at the indulgence
of the goddamn ownership.

22:31.288 --> 22:33.205
The lady's husband
would know.

22:37.705 --> 22:41.163
- How much do they want, Dave?
- Ten thousand dollars.

22:41.288 --> 22:44.246
I don't know what to do, Ed.
I don't know what I can do.

22:45.745 --> 22:47.912
You know,

22:48.037 --> 22:50.287
I know who
the son of a bitch is.

22:53.329 --> 22:56.079
You know... who who is?

22:56.162 --> 22:57.745
The son of a bitch.
The blackmailer.

22:57.870 --> 22:59.786
I know who he is.

22:59.869 --> 23:02.828
It's no one you know.
It's a businessman from Sacramento.

23:02.953 --> 23:04.911
A goddamn pansy, Ed.

23:07.286 --> 23:10.286
Tryin' to rope me
into some crackpot scheme.

23:10.578 --> 23:13.244
I heard him out,
then I told him to go to hell.

23:13.328 --> 23:16.786
The very next day
the very next day I get a note,
the blackmail note,

23:16.828 --> 23:19.243
