that we could hide from Ann.

24:22.616 --> 24:25.990
Doris, she was, she was pretty hot
about that, god bless her.

24:26.115 --> 24:28.782
Embezzlin', Ed.

24:28.907 --> 24:31.865
Embezzlin' from
my own goddamn wife.

24:36.949 --> 24:38.532
I'm sorry.

24:41.074 --> 24:42.739
I'm sorry.

24:44.073 --> 24:45.906
It's okay.

24:57.280 --> 25:00.197
In a way,
I felt bad for Big Dave.

25:00.280 --> 25:04.530
I knew that ten grand was going to
pinch him where it hurt,

25:04.613 --> 25:06.488
But Doris was two-timing me

25:06.613 --> 25:09.572
And I guess somewhere
that pinched a little too.

26:03.985 --> 26:05.694
That was pretty.

26:08.152 --> 26:09.819
Did you make that up?

26:09.944 --> 26:11.902
Oh, no.

26:12.027 --> 26:14.694
No, that was written
by Ludwig Van Beethoven.

26:20.027 --> 26:22.277
Well, it was quite something.

26:22.527 --> 26:25.026
Yeah, he wrote some
beautiful piano sonatas.

26:25.109 --> 26:28.109
That was really something.

26:33.109 --> 26:34.567
I'm Ed Crane.

26:34.650 --> 26:36.567
I know who you are, Mr. Crane.

26:36.650 --> 26:39.983
My father used to take me with him
when he went to get his hair cut.

26:40.108 --> 26:41.275
Walter Abundas?

26:41.525 --> 26:43.942
Oh, yeah, sure.
Walter.

26:45.067 --> 26:47.067
Yeah, I'm Rachel Abundas.

26:47.192 --> 26:49.150
But everyone call me Birdy.

26:50.317 --> 26:52.567
I'm sorry.
I just didn't remember.

26:52.650 --> 26:53.775
Oh, no, it's okay.

26:53.900 --> 26:58.817
You can't expect to remember
every skinny girl who comes in with her dad.

27:06.566 --> 27:08.899
So you don't, uh, like
that music out there?

27:09.024 --> 27:11.566
Not really.

27:11.691 --> 27:13.816
I'm not big on music, ordinarily.

27:14.857 --> 27:16.066
Ed.

27:28.773 --> 27:30.773
What a knucklehead.

27:31.606 --> 27:33.773
- Who?
- Dave.

27:35.190 --> 27:36.898
Why's that?

27:37.690 --> 27:39.147
Money problems.

27:39.272 --> 27:42.064
He's thinking about
canceling the annex.

27:42.939 --> 27:44.230
So?

27:45.272 --> 27:48.064
That means I don't run Nirdlingers.

27:53.730 --> 27:55.189
What a knucklehead.

28:01.022 --> 28:03.147
Big Dave did it, though.

28:08.688 --> 28:11.728
I sent a note telling him
where to drop the money.

28:13.728 --> 28:14.895
And he did.

28:14.978 --> 28:16.687
He came across.

28:55.686 --> 28:57.686
Yeah. Good!
How are ya?

28:57.769 --> 29:00.060
Come in.
I got everything organized.

29:00.143 --> 29:02.851
How you doin'?
You got a check?

29:02.935 --> 29:05.935
- Cash.
- Cash?

29:06.018 --> 29:08.935
Usually these kinds of things
are done with a bank draft,

29:09.018 --> 29:11.143
But cash, that's fine.

29:11.268 --> 29:13.268
It's all the same in the end.

29:14.935 --> 29:16.267
Dough is dough, huh?

29:18.100 --> 29:19.100
Whoa, nellie.

29:22.017 --> 29:23.850
I got the paperwork here.

29:23.934 --> 29:25.809
Partnership papers.

29:25.892 --> 29:27.642
They reflect our agreement.

29:27.767 --> 29:29.684
Fifty-fifty on the net.

29:29.767 --> 29:34.600
I provide professional services,
you provide the capital.

29:34.684 --> 29:38.100
I'm gonna give you a receipt
on the dough here.

29:38.225 --> 29:40.600
Uh, pretty straightforward.

29:40.684 --> 29:43.600
- I don't know whether you wanna show it to a lawyer
- No, that's okay.

29:43.684 --> 29:46.475
Yeah. Screw 'em, right?

29:46.600 --> 29:50.016
Pay them to tangle it up,
then you have to pay them to untangle them.

29:50.099 --> 29:52.098
What's the point?

29:52.182 --> 29:54.098
You just give me a second,

29:54.182 --> 29:56.890
I'll give you a receipt on the...

29:57.598 --> 29:58.723
Whoa, nellie.

30:00.098 --> 30:03.473
Okay, one thing
we didn't talk about was,

30:03.557 --> 30:06.473
I am thinking about,
uh, calling the place Tolliver's.

30:06.598 --> 30:08.223
After me, you know.

30:08.515 --> 30:12.557
I didn't think you were, uh,
much interested in, uh...

30:12.640 --> 30:16.057
- That's fine.
- Yeah, that's good. Good, good.

30:16.140 --> 30:19.640
Now, ready?
One second and I will...

30:19.765 --> 30:22.264
Okay, that's it.

30:24.014 --> 30:26.014
As per our discussion.

30:27.056 --> 30:28.764
All right, there it is,

30:28.889 --> 30:31.972
Writ large in legal escritoire.

30:32.097 --> 30:33.889
- And the, uh...
- Say, Creighton.

30:37.764 --> 30:39.639
You're not gonna screw me
on this.

30:41.639 --> 30:43.055
Screw you?

30:43.138 --> 30:44.513
Jesus.

30:46.263 --> 30:47.263
Take it to a lawyer.

30:47.555 --> 30:49.888
No, I insist!

30:49.971 --> 30:51.805
I insist!

30:51.888 --> 30:56.054
This is dry cleaning.
This is not some fly-by-night thing here.

30:57.304 --> 30:58.804
Oh, I'll tell you,

30:58.929 --> 31:02.720
I have been 13 years as an entrepreneur,
and I have never...

31:02.845 --> 31:04.137
- It's okay.
- Nobody's ever questioned me...

31:04.262 --> 31:06.595
Hey, you want the dough back?

31:06.679 --> 31:08.762
Huh? Huh? Do you know
who you're talkin' to here?

31:08.845 --> 31:11.137
Do you know who I am?
Do you have any idea who...

31:11.220 --> 31:12.554
It's okay.

31:13.929 --> 31:16.595
So, Tolliver's is okay, then?

31:20.262 --> 31:22.137
The next day was Saturday.

31:22.262 --> 31:25.054
We were going to a reception
for Doris's cousin Gina...

31:25.137 --> 31:28.178
Who just married a wop vendor
out near Modesto.

31:28.303 --> 31:30.803
Doris didn't much feel like going,
and I didn't either.

31:30.886 --> 31:35.052
But like she said,
we had a commitment.

31:37.093 --> 31:38.885
I hate wops.

31:42.260 --> 31:44.760
What's so goddamn strange
about that?

31:44.843 --> 31:46.218
I didn't say a word.

31:46.302 --> 31:48.510
You didn't have to
grow up with them.

31:50.552 --> 31:51.843
Family.

31:59.176 --> 32:01.801
Ed! Uncle Ed!

32:06.509 --> 32:10.134
He's riding Garibaldi!
Uncle Frankie's riding Garibaldi!

32:32.799 --> 32:34.882
That was when
she started drinking.

32:35.007 --> 32:35.799
Doris.

32:36.715 --> 32:37.549
Doris!

32:37.632 --> 32:39.674
You been okay?

32:39.757 --> 32:42.924
Mmm. Yeah.
How you doing, Costanza?

32:43.049 --> 32:46.257
Oh, you know.
Still got my health.

32:46.549 --> 32:48.715
And. Uh, how you been, uh...

32:49.882 --> 32:51.257
- Ed.
- Ed.

32:51.549 --> 32:53.965
He's a barber, right?

32:54.090 --> 32:57.715
It's a good trade.
So, how come you got no kids, huh?

32:57.799 --> 33:00.132
No, come on, kids!

33:00.215 --> 33:04.464
I- I just ate lunch!
I couldn't eat another thing.

33:04.548 --> 33:06.589
Oh, n... Anthony!

33:06.714 --> 33:09.089
Anthony, it's you!

33:09.214 --> 33:11.214
Okay, kids. Ready? And...

33:20.922 --> 33:25.130
Congratulations. Gina.
It's so goddamn wonderful.

33:25.213 --> 33:28.755
Life is just so goddamn wonderful,
You almost won't believe it.

33:28.880 --> 33:30.838
- It's just a bowl of goddamn cherries.
- Let' go.

33:30.922 --> 33:32.880
Sure.

33:35.797 --> 33:38.462
Congratulations on your goddamn cherries!

33:40.754 --> 33:42.546
Let go of my goddamn elbow!

33:54.504 --> 33:57.671
I never wanna see
another blueberry pie.

34:00.962 --> 34:04.212
I never even wanna hear those words.

34:07.754 --> 34:09.710
Don't say those words, Ed.

34:12.043 --> 34:14.043
Don't say those words.

35:03.250 --> 35:05.583
I'd met Doris blind
on a double date...

35:05.708 --> 35:09.250
With a loudmouthed buddy of mine
who was seeing a friend of hers from work.

35:09.542 --> 35:13.458
We went to a movie.
Doris had a flask.

35:13.583 --> 35:15.749
Boy, she could put it away.

35:19.166 --> 35:23.582
At the end of the night,
she said she liked that I didn't talk much.

35:23.707 --> 35:26.749
It was only a couple weeks later
she suggested we get married.

35:35.874 --> 35:37.166
Yeah.

35:37.249 --> 35:41.166
Ed, it's Big Dave.
I gotta talk to you.

35:41.249 --> 35:42.791
What?

35:43.624 --> 35:44.999
Now?

35:45.916 --> 35:48.123
Yeah. It's important.

35:48.915 --> 35:50.706
But it-it's...

35:50.831 --> 35:52.706
Please, Ed.

35:54.122 --> 35:55.955
Your place?

35:56.039 --> 35:57.997
I'm at the store.

35:58.122 --> 36:00.455
Let yourself in.

36:57.036 --> 36:58.202
Dave?

37:02.536 --> 37:04.119
I'm ruined.

37:07.911 --> 37:10.036
They've ruined me.

37:10.119 --> 37:11.994
This money.

37:13.161 --> 37:14.786
No annex.

37:15.744 --> 37:17.744
I'm all shot to hell.

37:19.702 --> 37:21.702
So, you paid the guy?

37:32.076 --> 37:34.035
What kind of man are you?

37:36.784 --> 37:38.909
What kind of man...

37:39.034 --> 37:40.492
Are you?

37:43.867 --> 37:46.950
I mean, I'd understand
if you came in here and...

37:47.075 --> 37:49.575
Socked me in the nose, whatever.

37:50.700 --> 37:52.534
I deserve it.

37:52.659 --> 37:55.200
I'm not proud of what I did.

37:56.741 --> 37:58.574
But you.

38:02.699 --> 38:04.033
Yeah, I paid up.

38:05.616 --> 38:07.491
As you well know.

38:09.283 --> 38:11.699
But then I went and
found the pansy.

38:17.949 --> 38:20.116
Oh, you got nothin' to say, huh?

38:20.241 --> 38:23.199
Well, you know the story.

38:24.074 --> 38:26.991
I didn't.

38:27.074 --> 38:29.697
I had to beat it
out of the pansy.

39:00.656 --> 39:02.530
I'm all shot to hell.

39:09.530 --> 39:11.238
Well, Dave, uh...

42:21.228 --> 42:25.020
It was only a couple weeks later
she suggested we get married.

42:28.936 --> 42:31.728
I said, "Don't you want
to get to know me more?"

42:31.853 --> 42:34.603
She said, "Why?
Does it get better?"

42:36.853 --> 42:38.770
She looked at me
like I was a dope,

42:38.895 --> 42:41.520
Which I never
really minded from her.

42:41.603 --> 42:44.520
And she had a point,
I guess.

42:44.603 --> 42:47.852
We knew each other
as well then as now.

42:47.894 --> 42:50.434
Anyway, well enough.

43:03.643 --> 43:06.726
Holy, moley,
do I got a headache.

43:06.851 --> 43:09.518
- How are you today, Ed?
- Okay.

43:10.851 --> 43:13.476
- You don't got a headache?
- No.

43:14.643 --> 43:17.809
Damn, I got a headache
to beat the band.

43:22.101 --> 43:25.642
Did you pump it? You can't pump it.
That'll just flood it.

43:25.725 --> 43:30.600
No, no, no, you gotta pump it.
You can't just hold it down.
I mean that'll flood it.

43:30.725 --> 43:33.100
You crazy?
You pump it.

43:33.225 --> 43:35.558
You can't hold it down.

43:36.892 --> 43:39.891
- Just turn the key.
